cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this protocol or build on it, please cite it as below."
title: "CSAE — Continuous Session-Attested Evidence: a protocol for attesting AI-generated commits to a verifiable audit chain"
abstract: "A coordination protocol for attesting AI-generated commits to a continuous audit chain. Combines pre-work intent registration (operator scope claim), bundle authoring (links commits to reviewer verdicts and scope claim via self-attestation), audit-mirror publication (separate tamper-evident repository), and server-side validator enforcement on canonical main. Composes with adversarial review (Russian Judge) and topology convergence (Peer-Worker Convergence) for end-to-end auditability of AI-assisted work."
authors:
